The paper proposes a method for improving the decoding performance of EEG signals in a brain computer interface (BCI) by utilizing a Denoising Autoencoder (DAE) for feature learning. This involves processing incomplete EEG data that has been contaminated by artefacts, which is a common problem in BCI research. The paper also mentions the use of spectral power estimation and filtering methods, which are commonly used in signal processing and machine learning. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
